Ferrovial, Metrovacesa and Fersa: Spanish Equity Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-08-05T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/ferrovial-metrovacesa-and-fersa-spanish-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  Spain ’s IBEX 35 fell 3.9 percent to 8,686.50.  Ferrovial SA (FER)  : Spain’s second-largest builder by
market capitalization said its Budimex unit bought Polish
railway builder PNI for 56 million euros ($79.3 million). The
shares dropped 3.7 percent to 8.12 euros.  Fersa Energias Renovables SA (FRS SM): The renewable energy
producer posted a first-half net profit of 2 million euros,
reversing a 1.98 million-euros loss a year earlier. The shares
retreated 6.3 percent to 90 euro cents.  Metrovacesa SA (MVC)  : Spain’s largest real estate
company by market value said it reached an agreement with
lenders to renegotiate 3.6 billion euros of debt. The shares
declined 5.5 percent to 1.55 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Andrew Blackman  at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 